vels reflect the process of release from her state of mourning for lost loved ones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAnger in literature. 0aCharacters and characteristics in literature. 0aCreativity in literature. 0aEmotions in literature. 0aGrief in literature. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturezEngland. 0aPsychoanalysis and literature. 0aPsychological fiction, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aPsychological fiction, English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBerman, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107169240 cprintz978081474194840uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814743973.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814743973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814743973/original  a978-3-11-071692-4  New York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK